sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Dashboard as Ray Head Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant Operator as CodeFlare Operator<br/>controller-runtime
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant CASecret as CA Secret<br/>(per-cluster)
    participant InitC as Init Container<br/>(head/worker pod)
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Node<br/>10001/TCP gRPC
    participant RayWorker as Ray Worker Node<br/>10001/TCP gRPC

    Note over User, Dashboard: Flow 1: RayCluster OAuth Dashboard Access (OpenShift)
    User->>Router: GET /dashboard<br/>HTTPS/443
    Router->>OAuth: Forward (reencrypt)<br/>HTTPS/8443
    Note right of OAuth: Validates OpenShift<br/>OAuth token
    OAuth->>Dashboard: Proxy request<br/>HTTP/8265 (localhost)
    Dashboard-->>OAuth: Dashboard response
    OAuth-->>Router: HTTPS response
    Router-->>User: Dashboard HTML

    Note over Operator, RayWorker: Flow 2: RayCluster mTLS Certificate Bootstrap
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Generate RSA 2048-bit CA cert<br/>ServiceAccount token auth
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Confirmed
    Operator->>CASecret: Create ca-secret-{cluster}<br/>CA key + certificate
    Note over InitC: Pod starts with<br/>CA cert volume mount
    InitC->>InitC: OpenSSL genrsa + req<br/>Generate per-pod server cert
    InitC->>InitC: OpenSSL x509 -CA<br/>Sign with cluster CA
    Note over RayHead, RayWorker: mTLS established between nodes
    RayHead->>RayWorker: gRPC/10001<br/>mTLS (per-pod certs)
    RayWorker-->>RayHead: Response<br/>mTLS (client cert)

    Note over User, RayWorker: Flow 3: Network Policy Enforcement
    Note right of RayHead: NetworkPolicy rules:<br/>1. Same ray.io/cluster pods: full access<br/>2. Same namespace: 10001, 8265<br/>3. KubeRay operator ns: 8265, 10001<br/>4. openshift-monitoring: 8080<br/>5. All sources: 8443 (OAuth), 10001 (mTLS)
